              "is_portal": false
            }
          },
          "npcs": []
        },
        "296": {
          "vnum": 296,
          "name": "The Rocky Hills",
          "description": "The rough terrain here makes travel difficult. The predominant vegetation consists of coarse, brown weeds and low, ragged bushes. A traveled path leads north and climbs toward some mountains in the distance. A steep trail leads down and toward the south, while a narrow path ventures eastward through the rocky hills, and a beaten path heads toward what appears to be a chasm to the west. A delicate golden flower opens toward the sky, its petals catching the light. You are riding atop a well-bred horse.",
